The yield on 46,000 hectares (ha) ofrapeseed in central China will be cut by up to 70 pct byhailstorms and tornadoes that swept across nearly 100,000 ha ofcrops on March 6, the New China News Agency said today.    The storm, which lashed the Huai and Yangtze rivers andeastern Anhui province, left two people dead and 800 othersinjured. Some 800 houses were flattened and 19 boats sunk, itsaid.    The Anhui provincial government has sent emergency reliefto the 19 counties affected, the news agency said. REUTER&#3;